author: Henry Zwartz
title: 'People will die': Chief Health Officer warns Northern Territorians failing to practise social distancing
description: The NT's Chief Health Officer warns Territorians are not taking COVID-19 seriously enough, saying "this virus holds no prisoners", as police begin checks on people in isolation.
content:
Posted 
March 30, 2020 07:46:25
The NT's top health officer says some Territorians are failing to practise strict physical-distancing rules, warning "people will die" from coronavirus unless everyone changes their behaviour.
